  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "What is a good website for free books?",
  "response": "There are several excellent websites where you can access free books legally. Here are some of the best ones:\n\n---\n\n### **General Free Books**\n1. **Project Gutenberg**  \n   - [www.gutenberg.org](https://www.gutenberg.org)  \n   - Offers over 70,000 free eBooks, focusing on older literary works that are in the public domain.\n\n2. **Internet Archive**  \n   - [archive.org](https://archive.org)  \n   - A vast digital library with millions of free books, including texts, audiobooks, and more.\n\n3. **Open Library**  \n   - [openlibrary.org](https://openlibrary.org)  \n   - Part of the Internet Archive, it provides access to millions of free books, including modern titles.\n\n4. **ManyBooks**  \n   - [manybooks.net](https://manybooks.net)  \n   - Offers over 50,000 free eBooks in various formats, including classics and contemporary works.\n\n---\n\n### **Academic & Educational Books**\n5. **Google Books**  \n   - [books.google.com](https://books.google.com)  \n   - Provides previews and full access to many books, especially those in the public domain.\n\n6. **LibreTexts**  \n   - [libretexts.org](https://libretexts.org)  \n   - Focuses on open-access textbooks and educational resources.\n\n7. **Open Textbook Library**  \n   - [open.umn.edu](https://open.umn.edu)  \n   - Offers free, peer-reviewed textbooks for academic subjects.\n\n---\n\n### **Specialized & Niche Books**\n8. **HathiTrust**  \n   - [hathitrust.org](https://hathitrust.org)  \n   - A partnership of academic and research institutions offering millions of free books.\n\n9. **Standard Ebooks**  \n   - [standardebooks.org](https://standardebooks.org)  \n   - Provides high-quality, beautifully formatted public domain eBooks.\n\n10. **BookBub**  \n    - [bookbub.com](https://www.bookbub.com)  \n    - Offers free and discounted eBooks from major retailers (requires account creation).\n\n---\n\n### **Children\u2019s Books**\n11. **International Children\u2019s Digital Library**  \n    - [en.childrenslibrary.org](http://en.childrenslibrary.org)  \n    - Free access to children\u2019s books from around the world.\n\n12. **Storynory**  \n    - [storynory.com](https://www.storynory.com)  \n    - Free audio stories for children.\n\n---\n\n### **Audiobooks**\n13. **Librivox**  \n    - [librivox.org](https://librivox.org)  \n    - Free public domain audiobooks read by volunteers.\n\n14. **Loyal Books**  \n    - [loyalbooks.com](https://www.loyalbooks.com)  \n    - Offers free audiobooks and eBooks of public domain works.\n\n---\n\nAlways check the copyright status of books to ensure they are legally available for free. Enjoy your reading! \ud83d\udcda\ud83d\ude0a",
  "temperature": 1.0,
